   "options": {
    "mode": "markdown",
    "content": "## 🧠 Fenrir — Are we actually learning?\nFenrir is **compounding** (real learning, not just recall) only if these move together over time: **Reuse ↑**, **Teacher-escalation ↓**, **Cost per solved ↓**, while **Skills ↑**. A flat **Reuse** curve is an honest *negative* result — recall, not compounding. _Benchmarks are contamination-unsafe, so absolute accuracy isn't a clean claim; the **trends** are the signal._"
   }
  },
  {
   "id": 2,
